                                                                           SAST (Static Application Security Testing) â€“ Line by Line

1. Scans the source code without running the app/website
2. Used early in development, before deployment
3. Detects code-level vulnerabilities
4. Helps developers find and fix issues during coding
5. Runs faster, easy to integrate into CI/CD
6. May show false positives (not always exploitable)
7. Needs access to code files or binaries
8. Cannot find runtime misconfigurations
9. Also called white-box testing


